<br>
Do I agree the city is right in withholding pay... NO.  But I also understand why they do.  For a city government to continue to give full pay and benefits to employees hurt OFF the job it would be necessary to raise taxes, considerably.  While the public hue and cry for this officer is probably quite high in his community, how many of those same folk crying &quot;foul&quot; would be willing to pay an additional 1%, 2% or more on their local taxes to defray the cost of continuing support?<br>
<br>
And the argument that if he had been uninjured and still working they'd have to pay him anyway does not work.  While he is out recuperating they are having to pay others to fill the position he normally holds.   <p>Mherina Whyndreaver<br>
